<div class="case-story__chapter">
  <p>Trackpacer is a digital "trackrabbit" that helps competitive runners train harder. It's comprised of a series of LED strips installed in a 400 meter track. The system projects a 3 meter beam of light that orbits the track at a pace chosen by the runner or their coach.</p>
</div>

<div class="case-story__chapter">
  <h2>My role</h2>
  <p>After a React-based prototype had been created, I was brought in to design the user interface and establish a vision for future features like saved workouts, system configuration, and an Apple Watch companion app.</p>
</div>

<div class="case-story__chapter">
  <h2>Passing control</h2>
  <p>One one person can control TrackPacer at a time. Allowing one person to take control when another is using the track is clearly a bad experience.</p>
  <p>The app polls to see whether the track is occupied and, if it is, only the "Request Control" action is presented. Tapping that sends a request to the current controller, who can pass control or ignore the request.</p>
